The paper deals with improving the performance of routing protocols in ad hoc wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). The paper also discusses the impact of packet loss and end-to-end delays on network performance, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm to improve the existing routing protocols, which is related to cryptography and security (CR) and social and information networks (SI).
